FINANCIAL INFORMATION ABOUT FOREIGN AND DOMESTIC OPERATIONS.

NET SALES IN THE U.S. ACCOUNT FOR APPROXIMATELY 37% OF TOTAL NET SALES.  NO OTHER INDIVIDUAL COUNTRY EXCEEDS 10% OF TOTAL NET SALES.  OPERATIONS OUTSIDE THE U.S. ARE GENERALLY CHARACTERIZED BY THE SAME CONDITIONS DISCUSSED IN THE DESCRIPTION OF THE BUSINESS ABOVE AND MAY BE AFFECTED BY ADDITIONAL FACTORS INCLUDING CHANGING CURRENCY VALUES, DIFFERENT RATES OF INFLATION, ECONOMIC GROWTH AND POLITICAL AND

